    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="859"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 909.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    835, of the 4th instant, in regard to the case of George Knapp at Bitlis, and to
                    approve your note of February 11 to Tevfik Pasha on the subject, a copy of which
                    you inclose.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
